name: Spokane Valley Mall
directions: The mall has two sets of restrooms -- both have a single gender neutral "family" restroom between the larger, multi-stall Men's and Women's. The restrooms on the first floor are on the east end: enter the doors by Azteca and head for the escalators. You'll see a hallway with a restroom sign over it on your right, and if you follow that hallway down a bit you'll find the mall management office and the restrooms. The restrooms on the second floor are on the west end: if you enter at the food court and take a right past Cinnamon, the restrooms will be down a short hall between Cinnabon and MasterCuts.

name: Kaw Prairie Community Church
directions:
From the lobby, facing the two main restrooms, with your back to the gym/sanctuary, there is a hallway on either side of the restrooms (near each of the check-in desks). 
If you take the hallway on the left, you will pass a checkin desk and a classroom on your left side, and there will be a restroom. Warning, it has three doors, so be sure to lock all of them, and knock first.
If you take the hallway on the right, you will walk past the play-place entrance and a classroom on your right, and there will be the bathroom.
comment: It is recommended you use the one on the right side (same side of the building as the play-place), since it only has one door, and the other restroom has 3.

name: De Soto High School
directions: Going down the main hallway, towards the majority of the classrooms, on the right hand side, across from Mr. Sullivan's room, there will be two doors. The second one is the Nurse's office. If you enter that door, take a left through the first doorway, and head towards the back of the office, there will be a restroom there.
comment: You may have to talk to the nurse in order to reach said restroom. Really only accessible for students while the nurse's office is open.

name: De Soto High School
directions: Go downstairs to the basement. (There is an elevator if needed.) The basement is shaped like a U. Find the middle of the U, and there will be a library facing a classroom with a glass wall. Go into the library. On the opposite side of the desk, between the copy room and the stocks is the bathroom. If you need help, the librarian is very nice.
comment: If you are visiting the library during class, you will have to sign in, so it would be advised to ask your professor to visit the library rather than the restroom, or to wait until passing period. You would have to be a student, teacher, or graduated student in order to use it, as it is within the school library. It is only available when the library is open.

name: De Soto High School
directions: Entering Student Services from the commons, walk straight back, as though you were going to see a counselor. The restroom is on the right hand side, and the hallway to visit the counselors will be on your left.
comment: Student services would have to be open in order for you to use said restroom, so it really only works during the school day for students and teachers. There is a lady at the desk in Student Services, but she is very nice.
